Interface ListInput<V,T>

  • Type Parameters:
    V - type of value object
    T - type of Item object
    All Superinterfaces:
    Input<V>, ItemInput<V,T>, SuggestedItemInput<V,T>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    OptionalListInput<V,T>, PreSelectInput<V,T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BasicTypeInput, CalendarFieldInput, CalendarMonthInput, ClassificationFactory.ClassificationCodeListInput, ClassInput, CodeListInput, ConstructedObjectInput, DataObjectFactory.AbstractDataObjectInput, DataObjectFactory.DataObjectInput, DataObjectFactory.SortingDataObjectInput, EnumInput, EnumIntegerInput, IntegerRangeInput, IntegerSetInput, ListInputWrapper, NullListInput, OnOffInput, OptionalFieldInput, OptionalIndexInput, OptionalListInputWrapper, RadioButtonInput, RepositoryFieldInput, RepositoryForeignKeyInput, RepositoryIndexInput, SetInput, StringListInput, TableInput, TypeProducerInput

    public interface ListInput<V,T>
extends SuggestedItemInput<V,T>
    Input that selects values from a List. For consistency the parse method should parse tag values. That is tags are String representations of the Input values. Each possible choice has 4 representations
    • The Value corresponding to the value stored in the Input
    • The Item is the target object e.g. the DataObject being selected. We sometimes need to call methods on these. For a simple list the Value and Item may be the same.
    • The tag which is a simple string used to identify the selection this can be used internally e.g. for HTML forms.
    • The text actually presented to the user.
